snippet: The House voted for the 62nd time to repeal the Affordable Care Act, in effect forcing a rare veto from the president to protect his signature domestic achievement.
abstract: House votes to repeal Affordable Care Act, marking 62nd such vote but first to reach Pres Obama's desk; vote, which will force Obama to veto measure, demonstrates ability of Congressional Republicans to override united Democratic front, force that could prove crucial if next president is Republican.
lead_paragraph: The House voted for the 62nd time to repeal the Affordable Care Act, in effect forcing a rare veto from the president to protect his signature domestic achievement.

headline.main: House Votes to Send Bill to Repeal Health Law to Obama’s Desk
headline.print_headline: House Bill Undoing Health Law Makes It to Obama
